<div class="container mt-5">
    <h1>About This Project</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        CineBox is a university project designed as a video streaming platform where users can manage and browse series.
        It is built using <strong>ASP.NET Core MVC</strong>, <strong>Entity Framework</strong>, and follows <strong>Clean Architecture</strong> principles.
        The project demonstrates efficient data management, user interaction, and clean code practices.
    </p>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Series Management:</strong> Users can add, edit, and delete series, with attributes such as title, producer, and genres.</li>
            <li><strong>Search & Filters:</strong> Provides search functionality by series name, producer, or genres for easy navigation.</li>
            <li><strong>YouTube Integration:</strong> Series are linked with video content from YouTube, allowing for seamless viewing directly from the platform.</li>
            <li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Utilizes <strong>Bootstrap 5</strong> for a user-friendly and responsive interface.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>ASP.NET Core MVC:</strong> For handling routing, controllers, and rendering views.</li>
            <li><strong>Entity Framework Core:</strong> For database management using code-first migrations and SQL Server.</li>
            <li><strong>Clean Architecture:</strong> A layered architecture separating concerns into application, domain, and infrastructure layers.</li>
            <li><strong>Bootstrap 5:</strong> For responsive and visually appealing UI design.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
        <h2>Purpose</h2>
        <p>This project was developed to apply best practices in software development, database management, and user interface design, as part of an academic assignment.</p>
    </section>

